on $n$.\n  Earlier multi-pass algorithms either have a large constant inside big-$O$\nnotation for the number of passes or the constant cannot be determined due to\nthe involved analysis, so our multi-pass algorithm should use much fewer passes\nfor approximation ratios bounded slightly below $2/3$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Feb 2017 18:48:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 18 Feb 2017 16:22:01 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 21 Apr 2017 15:19:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-24"}
