 comprehensive study, apart from the evolution, both mesonic and\nbaryonic components found to be non-extensive ($q>1$), besides the mass ordered\nhierarchy observed in the parameter $T$. We also study and compare in details\nthe theory-obtained parameters for the case of PYTHIA8 Monte Carlo Generator,\nperturbative QCD and quark coalescence models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Feb 2017 14:18:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 24 Feb 2017 16:09:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-27"}
